<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="222" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1405.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-16"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 16, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 28th ultimo, No. 940, transmitting addresses of the
                            Union and Emancipation Society of Manchester, and, in reply, to inform
                            you that your suggestion in regard to answering them is adopted.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>